The music the Cayman Islands Caribbean island chain includes wide selection international pop music well unique folk styles The Cayman National Cultural Foundation established 1984 helps preserve and promote Cayman folk music including the organisation festivals such Cayman Islands International Storytelling Festival the Cayman JazzFest Seafarers Festival and Cayfest There also Pirates Week Festival The Cayman JazzFest founded 2004 wellknown jazz festival that draws the islands deep connection with jazz The official national anthem the Cayman Islands God Save the Queen Beloved Isle Cayman words and music organist Leila RossShier the official national song The fiddle popular folk instrument Christmas music important part the Cayman folk tradition and consists serenading group singing Christmas carols Christmas Eve Instruments include the fiddle accordion mouth organ grater and drums There Cayman Music Entertainers Association which represent local musicians interests and professional studios such Hopscotch Studios offer recording and postproduction services Several local popular musicians are wellknown including Business Time Natasha Kozaily Bona Fide Cloudburst The Barefoot Man Chuck and Barrie aka Sea Heat and Nicholas Johnson 